    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">632.6231/42a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 17, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. Please comment briefly by cable on story in today’s issue of <hi
                        rend="italic">New York Times</hi> that the Brazilian Foreign Trade Council
                    has recommended “an emergency commercial agreement (with Germany) as a method of
                    selling surplus cotton stocks Germany is willing to buy with compensated
                    marks.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
